{"id":6494,"date":"2022-01-06T12:34:43","date_gmt":"2022-01-06T07:04:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/?p=6494"},"modified":"2022-01-06T12:35:05","modified_gmt":"2022-01-06T07:05:05","slug":"add-two-binary-numbers-golang","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/add-two-binary-numbers-golang\/","title":{"rendered":"Add two binary numbers program in Go (Golang)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_17 counter-hierarchy counter-decimal ez-toc-light-blue\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" style=\"display: none;\"><i class=\"ez-toc-glyphicon ez-toc-icon-toggle\"><\/i><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class=\"ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1\"><li class=\"ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2\"><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/add-two-binary-numbers-golang\/#Overview\" title=\"Overview\">Overview<\/a><\/li><li class=\"ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2\"><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/add-two-binary-numbers-golang\/#Program\" title=\"Program\">Program<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2 class=\"has-luminous-vivid-orange-color has-text-color has-large-font-size wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Overview\"><\/span><strong>Overview<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">The objective is to add two given binary numbers. Binary numbers are only composed of digits 0 and 1. Below is the binary addition logic for individual digits<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"has-medium-font-size wp-block-list\"><li>0+0 = Sum is 0, Carry is 0<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"has-medium-font-size wp-block-list\"><li>0+1 = Sum is 1, Carry is 0<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"has-medium-font-size wp-block-list\"><li>1+0 = Sum is 0, Carry is 0<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"has-medium-font-size wp-block-list\"><li>1+1 = Sum is 0, Carry is 1<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"has-medium-font-size wp-block-list\"><li>1+1+1 = Sum is 1, Carry is 1<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Examples<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-go\">Input: \"101\" + \"11\"\nOutput: \"1000\"\n\nInput: \"111\" + \"101\"\nOutput: \"1100\"<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"has-luminous-vivid-orange-color has-text-color has-large-font-size wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Program\"><\/span><strong>Program<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Below is the program for the same<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-go\">package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n)\n\nfunc addBinary(a string, b string) string {\n\tlenA := len(a)\n\tlenB := len(b)\n\n\ti := lenA - 1\n\tj := lenB - 1\n\n\tvar output string\n\tvar sum int\n\tcarry := 0\n\tfor i >= 0 && j >= 0 {\n\t\tfirst := int(a[i] - '0')\n\t\tsecond := int(b[j] - '0')\n\n\t\tsum, carry = binarySum(first, second, carry)\n\n\t\toutput = strconv.Itoa(sum) + output\n\t\ti = i - 1\n\t\tj = j - 1\n\t}\n\n\tfor i >= 0 {\n\t\tfirst := int(a[i] - '0')\n\n\t\tsum, carry = binarySum(first, 0, carry)\n\n\t\toutput = strconv.Itoa(sum) + output\n\t\ti = i - 1\n\n\t}\n\n\tfor j >= 0 {\n\t\tsecond := int(b[j] - '0')\n\n\t\tsum, carry = binarySum(0, second, carry)\n\n\t\toutput = strconv.Itoa(sum) + output\n\t\tj = j - 1\n\t}\n\n\tif carry > 0 {\n\t\toutput = strconv.Itoa(1) + output\n\t}\n\n\treturn output\n}\n\nfunc binarySum(a, b, carry int) (int, int) {\n\toutput := a + b + carry\n\n\tif output == 0 {\n\t\treturn 0, 0\n\t}\n\n\tif output == 1 {\n\t\treturn 1, 0\n\t}\n\n\tif output == 2 {\n\t\treturn 0, 1\n\t}\n\n\tif output == 3 {\n\t\treturn 1, 1\n\t}\n\n\treturn 0, 0\n}\n\nfunc main() {\n\toutput := addBinary(\"101\", \"11\")\n\tfmt.Println(output)\n\n\toutput = addBinary(\"111\", \"101\")\n\tfmt.Println(output)\n}<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Output<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-prismatic-blocks\"><code class=\"language-go\">1000\n1100<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Note: <\/strong>Check out our Golang Advanced Tutorial. The tutorials in this series are elaborative and we have tried to cover all concepts with examples. This tutorial is for those who are looking to gain expertise and a solid understanding of golang &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/golang-comprehensive-tutorial\/\">Golang Advance Tutorial<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Also if you are interested in understanding how all design patterns can be implemented in Golang. If yes, then this post is for you &#8211;<a href=\"https:\/\/golangbyexamples.com\/all-design-patterns-golang\/\">All Design Patterns Golang<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Table of Contents OverviewProgram Overview The objective is to add two given binary numbers. Binary numbers are only composed of digits 0 and 1. Below is the binary addition logic for individual&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"spay_email":"","footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_is_tweetstorm":false},"categories":[1],"tags":[3,4],"class_list":["post-6494","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-tech","tag-go","tag-golang"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v22.7 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Add two binary numbers program in Go (Golang) - Welcome To Golang By Example<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"in